[BID 1H] ⟦You open one\H with your five-card heart suit.⟧ Partner responds one\S, showing four or more spades.
[BID 2D] ⟦Over partner's one\S you bid two\D, a natural second suit.⟧ Partner bids the fourth suit, three\C, Fourth Suit Forcing and game-going, asking for more.
[BID 3S] ⟦You hold ace and two small spades, so you raise to three\S to show three-card support for partner's major.⟧ Partner, knowing of the fit, bids four\S.
[BID 4N] ⟦With three aces and a source of tricks you press on with four\N, Roman Keycard Blackwood for spades.⟧ Partner shows two keycards but denies the spade queen.
[BID 6S] ⟦Every keycard is present and your controls are rich, so you accept the small risk of the missing trump queen and bid six\S.⟧
[show NESW]All the aces and the trump king were there, and your diamonds and heart ace filled out the tricks, so six\S was well judged; it brought home twelve tricks. The missing queen was a minor worry that the strong eight-card fit easily absorbed.}
